This paper is about improving the complexity of the Learning with Errors problem, which is a fundamental problem in cryptography. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of lattice sieving techniques, which are related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions the Blum-Kalai-Wasserman algorithm, which is a computational complexity theory algorithm (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG).
